This paper involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques to extract commonsense knowledge from text, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves knowledge base completion, which falls under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a model to fuse information from both sequence text and existing knowledge base resource suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to extract knowledge from text, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of empirical results to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed model suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
